<P><P><B>
<BR><H1><I>REINVENTION EXPRESS EXTRA</I></H1><P><H1>Calendar	Sept 9, 1996 </H1><P>  <BR>
An Information Sheet for Federal Communicators, Managers, Workers, and Their Partners--Pass It On 
<h2>
     REINVENTION EXPRESS EXTRA 
<p> 
       September 9, 1996 
<p>
       
     
     Available Via Live Satellite Broadcast </h2>
<p>
     1996 National Partnership Awards To Be Presented in White House 
     Ceremony on September 11
             The National Partnership Council will honor top federal 
     labor-management teams from across the nation in a ceremony at The 
     White House Old Executive Office Building on September 11. The 1996 
     National Partnership Awards will go to the winning teams for their 
     achievements in streamlining programs, empowering front-line 
     employees, improving customer service, and cutting costs.
   <P>  
     Satellite Information 
             The ceremony will be broadcast live via satellite from 3 - 4 
     p.m., ET. The test pattern will begin at 2:30 p.m., ET.
             The satellite coordinates are:
  <P>   
     C-Band
  <P>
             Telstar 401, 97 degrees west
             Transponder 17 vertical
             Downlink frequency 4040 MHz Vertical
             Audio 6.2/6.8
  <P>   
     KU-Band
 <P> 
            SBS6, Orbital Slot 74 degrees west
             Transponder 11 horizontal
             Downlink 11970 horizontal
             Audio 6.2/6.8
  <P>  
     Closed captioning is available. Check with your viewing location prior 
     to the broadcast. For technical questions, call (202) 887-8700. For 
     more information, call the Center for Partnership and Labor-Management 
     Relations, U.S. Office of Personnel Management, (202) 606-2930.
 <P>    
     
     To subscribe to the Express by e-mail send an e-mail message to: 
     Listproc@etc.fed.gov with this message: SUBSCRIBE EXPRESS-L FIRSTNAME 
     LASTNAME. (Put three spaces: after the word "SUBSCRIBE," after 
     "EXPRESS-L," and after your FIRSTNAME.) For more information, contact 
     Pat Wood, National Performance Review, 750-17th St., NW, Washington, 
     DC 20006, (202) 632-0223; FAX: (202) 632-0390; e-mail: 
     pat.wood@npr.gsa.gov. The Express is also on the Internet at 
     http://www.npr.gov. Go to "News Room."
     
    
