<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<BR><H1><I>REINVENTION EXPRESS</I></H1><P><H1>Calendar	Sept 5, 1996 </H1><P>  <BR>
An Information Sheet for Federal Communicators, Managers, Workers, and Their Partners--Pass It On 

     
<h2>September 26: INNOVATIONS IN GOVERNMENT CONFERENCE
<p>
(Deadline extended until September 13)</h2>
<p>
   
     Federal, state, and local government workers are invited to a 
     Government Innovations Conference sponsored by the Bureau of 
     Reclamation on September 26 in San Antonio with the cooperation of the 
     Federal Executive Board. Cost is $40, which includes lunch. As a 
     winner of a 1995 Innovations in Government Award, the Bureau received 
     a $100,000 Ford Foundation Grant that it is using to underwrite the 
     conference and other activities. For more information, contact (801) 
     524-6934 or (801) 524-5561.
<p>     
     * * * * *
<p>     
     
<h2> September 30: ALIGNING THE GOVERNMENT PERFORMANCE AND RESULTS ACT <P>
     (GPRA) AND OTHER MANAGEMENT SYSTEMS WITH A CUSTOMER FOCUS </h2>
<p>     
     WHAT: Free conference sponsored by the National Performance Review for 
     all federal employees to discuss how we align our management 
     philosophy and systems to become a customer-focused organization. Our 
     speakers will be:
<p>     
     Anne Shields, President's Management Council John Koskinen, Office of 
     Management and Budget Greg Woods, National Performance Review
     Jerry Mechling, Harvard University      
<p>     
     WHEN:  Monday, September 30, 1996 from 9 - 11 AM.
<P>     
     WHERE:  Capital Hilton
     Presidential Ballroom
     16th and K Street NW
     Washington, DC 20004-2601
     Metro:  Red Line - Farragut North
     Orange and Blue Lines - Farragut West
<P>     
     WHO:  All employees involved in customer service, budget, strategic 
     planning, human resource management, GPRA and other management 
     systems.
<P>
     
     QUESTIONS:  Call the NPR Help Desk at 202-632-0150.
<P>     
     REGISTER:  Complete the form below. Please send this to all of your 
     federal colleagues!!
<P>     
     
     Registration Form
<PRE>     
     Please return this form to register for the "Aligning Customer Focus" 
     Conference so we can anticipate the number of seats required.  There 
     is no cost for this conference.
     
     Name__________________________________________________________
     
     Organization _________________________________________________
     
     Phone ________________________________________________________
     
     Fax __________________________________________________________
     
     Return to "Customer Service" Conference at NPR. (FAX 202-632-0390 or 
     e-mail: candy.kane@npr.gsa.gov)
     
