<HEAD>
<TITLE>	Reinvention Express Calendar, August 21, 1996</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<P>

<H1><I>REINVENTION EXPRESS</I></H1>
<P>
<H1>Calendar	August 21, 1996 </H1>
<P>  <BR>
An Information Sheet for Federal Communicators, Managers, Workers, and Their Partners--Pass It On <BR>

<P>
<H2>September 10-11: National Pollution Prevention Conference Celebrates Government-Private Sector Partnerships</H2>
<P>
<P>A national conference, &quot;Putting Pollution Prevention into Action,&quot; will be held at the Washington Hilton and Towers, Washington, DC, September 10-11.  A program highlight is the Industry 33/50 Celebration Dinner. The 33/50 Program is the Environmental Protection Agency's highly successful voluntary pollution prevention program embraced by more than 1,300 industry partners. The program, which called for reducing environmental releases of 17 high-volume toxic chemicals by 33 percent in 1993 and 50 percent in 1995, reached its goal a year early. (See Reinvention Express, June 27, 1996, Vol. 2, No. 16.)<BR>

<P>For more information on the conference, contact (703) 683-6695 or <I>cpruett@hampshire.org.</I> For information on 33/50, call Chris Tirpak at (202) 250-7538.<BR>

<P>*****<BR>

<P>
<H2>September 16-19: &quot;Balanced Scorecard&quot; Conference in Boston</H2>
<P>
<P>This conference, which features using the &quot;Balanced Scorecard&quot; in measuring corporate performance, is set for Boston on September 16-19. The conference theme is from a book by the same name in which authors Kaplan and Norton describe how organizations can translate strategy into action. For information, contact (800) 882-8684 or e-mail:<I> info@iqpc.com</I>.<BR>

<P>*****<BR>

<P>
<H2>September 16-19: 3rd Annual National Business Process Reengineering Conference and Exposition</H2>
<P>
<P>This conference, set for September 16-19 in Washington, DC, features best practices in industry and government for breakthrough performance. For information, contact (703) 761-0646 or e-mail: <I>ER@reengineering.com</I>.<BR>

<P>*****<BR>

<P>
<H2>September 17: Federal Editors Network Organizational Meeting</H2>
<P>
<P>The National Performance Review is organizing a federal editors network. An organizational meeting will be held at the White House Conference Center in Washington, DC, on September 17. The network is for editors of internal printed and electronic publications that reach federal workers.<BR>

<P>For information, contact Pat Wood at (202) 632-0223 or <I>pat.wood@npr.gsa.gov o</I>r contact Cindy Saboe at (202) 632-0323 or <I>cindy.saboe@npr.gsa.gov</I>. To be included in the network (whether you come to the meeting or not), fax or e-mail your name, organization,  mailing address, phone, fax, and e-mail address. Include a one-sentence description of your publication (or news service), including purpose, format, audience, and size of circulation. Our fax number is (202) 632-0390. Don't resubmit this information if you have already given it to us.<BR>

<P><B>*****</B><BR>

<P>
<H2>September 26: Innovations in Government Conference </H2>
<P>
<P>Federal, state, and local government workers are invited to a Government Innovations Conference sponsored by the Bureau of Reclamation on September 26 in San Antonio with the cooperation of the Federal Executive Board. Cost is $40, which includes lunch. As a winner of a 1995 Innovations in Government Award, the Bureau received a $100,000 Ford Foundation Grant that it is using to underwrite the conference and other activities. For more information,  contact (801) 524-6934 or (801) 524-5561.<BR>

<P>*****<BR>

<P>
<H2>October 10: Quality Pioneer Dr. J.M. Juran Will Be on Live, International Satellite Broadcast</H2>
<P>
<P>Dr. J.M. Juran will draw from his 70-year career to speak on quality--yesterday, today, and tomorrow in a satellite broadcast on October 10. Panelists include Dr. Curt W. Reimann, who directed the Malcolm Baldrige National Quality Award at the National Institute of Standards and Technology from 1987-95. Sponsored by the American Society for Quality Control and others, the broadcast is from 1 - 3:30 p.m., ET. For more information, contact Kristen Trulby at (800) 325-1533 or e-mail: i<I>nfo@iil.com</I>. The Web address is: <I>http://www.iil.com</I>.<BR>

<P>*****<BR>

<P>
<H2>October 15-17: 4th Annual Quality Air Force Symposium &amp; Expo</H2>
<P>
<P>The 4th Annual Quality Air Force Symposium and Expo '96 will be at the Civic Center in Montgomery, AL,  October 15 - 17. The theme is &quot;Quality Air Force in the 21st Century: Technology &amp; Innovation.&quot; For program and registration information, contact (800) 204-2005. Exhibitors should call (810) 656-1700.<BR>

<P>*****<BR>

<P>
<H2>November 18-20: Strategic Planning for Government</H2>
<P>
<P>The 5th National Conference on Strategic Planning for Government: Complying with the Government Performance and Results Act will be November 18-20 in Washington, DC. It will feature case studies from NASA, the Social Security Administration, Army Armament Research, Development and Engineering Center (1996 President's Quality Award winner), and the Department of Defense. For information, call (800) 420-2145 or visit this Web site: <I>http://www.iqpc.com</I>.<BR>

<P>*****<BR>

<P>
<H2>November 18-20: GOAL/QPC'S  Annual Conference</H2>
<P>
<P>GOAL/QPC's Annual Conference is November 18-20 in Orlando, FL. The theme is &quot;Lessons from Leaders: Building Adaptive Organizations to Thrive in Turbulent Markets.&quot;<BR>
Participants will hear presentations on quality success stories from many sectors, including  military, government, education, and health care. For more information, call (800) 643-4316.<BR>

<P>All calendar events are for information only and do not imply endorsement. To subscribe to the Express by e-mail send an e-mail message to:<I> Listproc@etc.fed.gov</I> with this message: <I>SUBSCRIBE EXPRESS-L FIRSTNAME LASTNAME</I>. (Put three spaces: after the word &quot;SUBSCRIBE,&quot; after &quot;EXPRESS-L,&quot; and after your FIRSTNAME.) For more information, contact Pat Wood, National Performance Review, 750-17th St., NW, Washington, DC 20006, (202) 632-0223; FAX: (202) 632-0390; e-mail: pat.wood@npr.gsa.gov. The <I>Express </I>is also on the Internet at <I>http://www.npr.gov</I>. Go to &quot;News Room.&quot;
<P>
<P>
