<HEAD>
<TITLE>	Reinvention Express Calendar, May 3, 1996</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<P>

<P>
<H4>REINVENTION EXPRESS</H4>
<P>
<H1>May Calendar	May 3, 1996 </H1>
<P>
<P>  <BR>
An Information Sheet for Federal Communicators, Managers, Workers, and Their Partners--Pass It On <BR>

<P>
<H2><B>May 6-12: Public Service Recognition Week</B></H2>
<P>	&quot;I salute our nation's public employees for their commitment to the American ideal of service and thank them for the invaluable contributions they make each day to the quality of our national life,&quot; said President Clinton as we begin Public Service Recognition Week, May 6-12. More than 1,200 cities will pay tribute to the nation's 20 million federal, state, and local government employees.<BR>
	In Washington, DC, the Interagency Mall Celebration will run from May 9-11, with a  kick-off  ceremony on the Mall at 11:30 a.m. on May 9. Supervisors in the area have authority to grant administrative leave to federal employees for the Mall Event, which includes more than 100 exhibits open from 10 a.m. until 5 p.m. each day. <BR>
	The week is sponsored by the Public Employees Roundtable, a non-profit, non-partisan coalition of 37 management and professional associations representing more than one million public employees. For more information, call PER at (202) 927-5000.<BR>

<P>
<H2><B>May 6: Vice President Gore Presents Awards</B></H2>
<P>	The Vice President will present Public Service Excellence Awards to six groups of government employees whose programs exhibit the highest standards of dedication, excellence, and accomplishment. The winners in each category are:<BR>

<P><B>Federal</B>--Federal Emergency Management Agency Assistance Program<BR>
<B>State</B>--New York State Department of Transportation A+B Bidding Program<BR>
<B>County</B>--Dallas County Hospital District's Community Oriented Primary Care Program<BR>
<B>City</B>--Monrovia (CA) Police Department's Community Activist Policing Program<BR>
<B>Intergovernmental</B>--Arizona Department of Revenue and Southwest District IRS<BR>
Federal/State Program<BR>
<B>International</B>--U.S. General Accounting Office's Office of International Audit<BR>
Organization Liaison<BR>

<P><B>Awards Ceremony Is on Satellite Broadcast</B><BR>
	The awards  will be presented at a breakfast ceremony in Washington, DC, on May 6. The event will be broadcast by delayed satellite television at 2:45 p.m. EDT. Here is the information:<BR>

<P>Ku Satellite, Telestar 401 Transponder 11, Position 97 West, Downlink Frequency 12040<BR>
Audio 6.2 and 6.8. The Satellite window is from 2:30 to 3:30 p.m.  <BR>

<P><B>For More Information</B><BR>
	For information about the satellite broadcast, call Michael Messinger at (202) 632-0150. For information about the awards, call Gretchen Hakola at PER, (202) 927-5000.	MORE...<BR>

<P><B>Reinvention Express Calendar, May 3, 1996, Page 2</B><BR>

<P>
<H2><B>May 14: Symposium on Managing in a Changing Workplace </B>	Mc-Graw-Hill  is sponsoring an all-day Symposium on Information Solutions for government managers at the Washington Convention Center in Washington, DC, on May 14. The theme is &quot;Managing Successfully in a Changing Workplace.&quot;</H2>
<P>	Speakers and panelists from government and business will conduct sessions on business process reengineering, budget issues for the 90's, job skills for the 21 century, role of the Internet, and other topics. Admission is complimentary. You may respond to an invitation on the Internet at <I>http://www.mcgraw-hill.com </I>or call (800) 514-2187 or send an email message to: <I>tthom@mh.com</I> (include your name, title, organization, address,  phone, and fax).<BR>

<P>
<H2><B>May 28: Transforming Government Conference</B></H2>
<P>	The Consortium for Cultural Change will sponsor a free all-day conference for government reinventors on May 28 at the NIH Natcher Center in Bethesda, MD.   You'll buy lunch in the cafeteria and pay $10 for the breaks and reception. Call Dr. Lynn S. Kahn at (202) 358-5259. The registration form is in the April 3 <I>Express</I>  (Vol. 2, No. 10) on the Internet at <I>http://www.npr.gov</I> (See News Room).<BR>

<P>
<H2><B>Coming in June </B></H2>
<P>June 3-6<B>:  Ninth Annual  National Conference on Federal Quality</B> at the Washington Hilton and Towers in Washington, DC. <B>Slots are still available</B>. The conference is open to the private sector as well as federal, state, and local government employees. For fee and other information, call Conference Coordinator Kim Exeter at (703) 312-7333 or Clint Sidwell at (703) 312-7329. <BR>

<P>June 19-20:  <B>1996 Franchising Conference</B> in Washington, DC. The theme is &quot;The Future of Reimbursable Government Services.&quot; The conference is for agency managers seeking to procure common administrative services from outside sources, and from other federal, state, and local government providers. For the fee schedule and registration information, call (301) 220-1701.<BR>

<P>June 19: <B>Satellite Broadcast: &quot;Are You Prepared for an Uncertain Future?&quot;</B> 1:00-2:30 p.m. The Interagency Advisory Group will present the nuts and bolts of career transition for federal employees and what we can all do to prepare ourselves for new careers, if necessary.<BR>

<P><B>C-band</B>: Satellite Telstar 401, Transponder 7, Channel 7, Downlink Frequency 3840, Polarity: Vertical, Position: 97 West, Audio: 6.2 and 6.8.<BR>
<B>KU-Band</B>: Satellite: SBS-6, Transponder 15, Channel 15, Downlink Frequency: 12068, Polarity: Horizontal; Position: 74 West, Audio: 6.2 and 6.8.<BR>
	If you would like to submit questions in advance or want more details on the broadcast, send a fax to (202) 720-9148. <BR>

<P>This is our first Reinvention Express Calendar. All events are for information only. Subscribe to the Express by email  and share it with others.  Send an email message to:<I>Listproc@etc.fed.gov</I> with this message: <I>SUBSCRIBE EXPRESS-L FIRSTNAME LASTNAME</I>. (Put three spaces: after the word &quot;SUBSCRIBE,&quot; after &quot;EXPRESS-L,&quot; and after your FIRSTNAME.) For more information, contact Pat Wood, National Performance Review, 750-17th St., NW, Washington, DC 20006, (202) 632-0223; FAX: (202) 632-0390; email: pat.wood@npr.gsa.gov. The <I>Express </I>is also on the Internet at <I>http://www.npr.gov</I>. <BR>

<P>
